        "description": "The Energy Company Obligation (ECO) is a government energy efficiency scheme designed to tackle fuel poverty and help reduce carbon emissions, which is currently in its 4th iteration, ECO4, running from April 2022 to March 2026. Over the last year the council has identified several opportunities and made significant progress on drawing investment for Birmingham's homes through the ECO retrofit programme. Building on our previous experience with ECO and learning from best practice examples from other local authorities, including Greater Manchester Combined Authority and Liverpool City Council, Birmingham City Council took the bold decision to procure ECO installer partners to deliver home retrofit measures. The two partners have already commenced installations across the city and are working with the council, communities and other stakeholders, to drive the delivery of energy efficiency measures to Birmingham homes. The initiative aims to harness \u00a345m per year of private investments, achieve estimated fuel bill savings of \u00a31.2m, and reduce the carbon emissions from the city's homes by 4,500 tonnes per year.",
