        "focusAreas": "Other: housing sector|Energy|Emissions reduction|Agriculture|Building and Infrastructure",
        "description": "Action 12 in the climate action plan is to run the Cosy homes in Lancashire programme to improve energy efficiency in domestic properties and support respiratory and mental health improvements. Cosy Homes in Lancashire is collaboration between local authorities - Wyre, Pendle, Lancashire which has contracted RHEA projects to offer energy efficient home improvements like heat pumps, energy efficient boilers and appliances to residents in need. It uses targeted allocations to ensure residents in most need receive support and has a regional remit to ensure wider equity between rural and urban residents. Events and education initiatives take place to publicize the wide range of energy efficient measures. Blackpool Council lead on the delivery and evaluation of the project and specifically report and action on inequalities in mitigation and adaption. ",
