        "description": "A multi-functional project working group has been established (involving internal and external partners) to support the development of climate action plans in schools. \\nThis is in line with the Department for Education's requirement that all educational establishments have climate action plans in place by 2025 -\\n\\nhttps://www.gov.uk/guidance/sustainability-leadership-and-climate-action-plans-in-education\\n\\nCollaborators include:\\n- Department for Education\\n- Elected members\\n- Leeds Trinity University - Climate Adapted Pathways for Education.\\n- Sister projects of DfE - Let's Go Zero, Climate Ambassadors, National Education Nature Park.\\n- Bradford Council programme leads such as Clean Air Schools Programme, Living Well Schools, Active Travel, Skills House.\\n- Community Groups such as 'Grow to School'\\n- Multi-Academy Trusts\\n- Keep Britain Tidy - Count Your Carbon\\n- Energy providers - 1Energy, Solar for Schools.\\n\\nBradford District Schools' Climate Action Event will take place on 6th November 2025, hosted by Bradford Council and include key partners and over 50 school settings. This event will support and facilitate the work to deliver climate action plans in schools as required by Department for Education. ",
