        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Industry|Building and Infrastructure|Energy|Adaptation|Emissions reduction",
        "description": "Bradford Council secured funding of almost \u00a31million from Innovate UK in 2024 and successfully led the formation and development of Bradford Manufacturing Futures (BMF) and appointed consultants to develop a district-wide industrial decarbonisation roadmap and investment prospectus.\\n\\nBMF is a cross-sector partnership of nine local organisations, including established industry leaders and the University of Bradford, who have come together to develop the Local Industrial Decarbonisation Project (LIDP). \\n\\nKey stages of LIDP included stakeholder engagement, emissions analysis and site surveys to understand the manufacturing energy demands and decarbonisation intervention opportunities, such as fuel switching technology. \\n\\nThe partnership provides a platform to share the responsibility and knowledge to support the transition to renewable energy sources for 30 manufacturers in some of the highest emitting sectors, including chemicals, food, basic metals, mineral products and metal fabrication, which produce 52% of the district's CO2 emissions. This includes exploring the possibilities around capturing and/or utilising CO2 emissions and repurposing heat that might otherwise be wasted.\\n\\nKey achievements include:\\n-A district-wide industrial Decarbonisation Pathway outlining how manufacturing-related emissions could be reduced by over 90% by 2040.\\n\\n-An Investment Prospectus which identifies opportunities in renewable energy and low-carbon technologies, such as heat pumps, solar PV, wind, hydrogen, and biomethane - to protect 24,000 jobs and create further employment growth.\\n\\n-Creation of five geographical Clean Growth Hubs, representing over 30 manufacturers. \\n\\n-Establishment of \\'Sustainability Leaders of the Future\\' programme to nuture tomorrow's local talent. \\n\\nBradford is recognised by the Government's Department for Energy Security and Net Zero as one of 13 key industrial clusters in England with strategic potential for decarbonisation. \\n\\nhttps://www.bradfordcluster.co.uk/\\n\\nSince the conclusion of LIDP and launch of BMF in February 2025, BMF is now established as a not-for-profit limited company and aims to drive clean growth in manufacturing. Its overarching goals are to:\\n-Be the trust voice of industry for Bradford District.\\n-Champion all manufacturers and share expertise \\nto sustain industrial prosperity within the district.\\n-Through collaboration and investment, drive the transition to net zero via energy efficiency and fuel switching technology.\\n-Inspire the next generation of talented leaders in sustainable manufacturing. \\n\\nNow with an established BMF board, it aims to achieve its goals by attracting funding and growing its membership and developing three dedicated interest groups which will focus on energy efficiency, fuel switching and SME clean growth.\\n\\nhttps://www.bradfordcluster.co.uk/",
        "otherEntities": "Energy|Academia|Climate initiatives/networks|Education sector|Regional government|Local government within country/area"
