        "focusAreas": "Energy|Building and Infrastructure|Emissions reduction|Finance",
        "description": "City of York Council is participating in the UK Shared Prosperity Fund led by the UK Government. The UK Shared Prosperity Fund (UK SPF) is a central pillar of the UK government's ambitious Levelling Up agenda and a significant component of its support for places across the UK. This scheme will support York local businesses via the following mechanisms:Supporting decarbonisation and improving the natural environment whilst growing the local economy. Taking a whole systems approach to invest in infrastructure to deliver effective decarbonisation across energy, buildings and transport and beyond, in line with our legally binding climate target. Maximising existing or emerging local strengths in low carbon technologies, goods and services to take advantage of the growing global opportunity.Green skills courses targeted around ensuring we have the skilled workforce to achieve the government's net zero and wider environmental ambitions.",
