        "focusAreas": "Food|Transport (Mobility)|Education|Energy|Waste|Public health|Adaptation|Building and Infrastructure|Resilience|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Natural environment|Emissions reduction",
        "description": "The York Climate Commission is an independent body, representing and reflecting the public, private and civic sectors from across the city.The Commission has an important role in reviewing and agreeing the York Climate Change Strategy and providing leadership and accountability for progressing the activity within the strategy and action plan.Commissioners play a role in identifying resources, creating a network of co-operation and collaboration, sharing knowledge and best practice and positioning the city as a leader in climate change.The work of York Climate Commission supports York's Climate Change Strategy and the work of the regional Yorkshire and Humber Climate Commission. The York Climate Commission relaunched in January 2024, and now has working groups across the following sectors Biodiversity/Nature; Buildings and Retrofit; Connecting With Green Spaces; Education and Youth Engagement; Energy; Food; Future Green Economy; Health and Climate Change; Transport; Waste and Circular Economy.",
