        "description": "Cornwall's new waste collection service is designed to enhance sustainability, reduce environmental impact, and contribute to climate change mitigation. Extensive public consultations via roadshows and face-to-face interactions were carried out across Cornwall detailing the new waste service. Feedback from the consultation helped to inform the implementation plan. The plan has been rolled out across Cornwall in zones, starting in 2023. The new service has already increased recycling rates and is now offering a weekly food waste collection. The service aims to reduce carbon emissions by 18,000 tonnes per annum. Local Nature Partnership is working with the industry and partners to increase waste reduction and recycling strategies further and embed the Local Nature Partnership Materials Charter to help create a more circular economy - including improving recycling rates. They are working with partners to help tackle sources of pollution such as run-off, soil erosion, sewage, plastics and industry (eg legacy mining) https://www.cornwall.gov.uk/rubbish-recycling-and-waste/new-food-waste-recycling-and-rubbish-service/why-we-re-changing-your-waste-collection-service/",
