        "description": "Marine Health - Alongside development of the Local Nature Recovery Strategy, the Local Nature Partnership supported the development of a voluntary Marine Nature Recovery Framework (MNRF). Led by Cornwall Council and supported by the Cornwall and Isles of Scilly Marine and Coastal Partnership (CIOS MCP), the MNRF sets out a shared vision for restoring and protecting our marine and coastal environments. It identifies priority habitats and species, maps opportunities for nature recovery, and outlines actions to support sustainable marine management across the region. The MNRF complements the statutory Cornwall and Isles of Scilly Nature Recovery Strategy and supports national goals such as the target to have 30% of land, rivers, and seas well managed for nature by 2030. The Framework is out for consultation from August to October 2025. \\n\\nWe continue to support the ongoing development and implementation of fisheries management plans, initiatives to tackle marine pollution, commission studies to understand the health of our seas and climate adaptation projects in the marine environment such as sea-grass restoration. \\n\\nhttps://letstalk.cornwall.gov.uk/cornwall-and-the-isles-of-scilly-marine-nature-recovery-framework\\n",
        "otherEntities": "NGO and associations|Academia|Other: Maritime Association|Residents/community groups|Climate initiatives/networks|Public authority"
