        "focusAreas": "Education|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Natural environment|Ecosystem restoration|Agriculture|Adaptation|Emissions reduction|Forestry|Resilience",
        "description": "Natural Climate Solutions - We are actively promoting nature-based solutions to climate change that work with and enhance natural processes.\\n\\nForest for Cornwall - More than 1.6m trees in nearly 1,000 locations have been planted as part of the Forest for Cornwall (https://www.cornwall.gov.uk/environment/countryside/forest-for-cornwall-programme/)which is celebrating its fifth anniversary. \\n\\nResidents, farmers, landholders, community groups and organisations have all contributed by growing tree saplings in fields, farms, towns, villages, schools, parks and gardens. \\n\\nA new map listing Forest for Cornwall planting projects has been produced showing the breadth and variety of places that have benefitted from increased tree cover. \\nhttps://www.cornwall.gov.uk/council-news/environment-culture-and-planning/new-map-shows-16m-trees-planted-across-the-region-for-forest-for-cornwall/\\n\\nCornish Hedge Survey - Cornwall Council is working with Cornwall Rural Education & Skills Trust (CREST), to help build a map of all the different hedging styles found in Cornwall. A Cornish Hedge survey has been recreated where we are asking people to take to photograph along with the location, enabling CREST to train people to build the right hedge for the right place.\\n\\nWe continue to explore and develop solutions to provide natural on-land carbon sequestration and adaptation landscapes (including plants and soils), as well as delivering marine-based carbon sequestration.https://www.cornwall.gov.uk/environment/countryside/forest-for-cornwall-programme/",
