        "mechanisms": "Policy and regulation development/ implementation|Other: Local Area Energy Strategy Development|Collaborative initiative|Reporting of climate and/or environmental data|Knowledge or data sharing",
        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Agriculture|Transport (Mobility)|Energy|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Landscape and jurisdictional approaches|Emissions reduction|Food|Natural environment",
        "description": "Residents' Energy Panel - in February and March 2024 a representative sample of 42 residents participated in a Residents' Energy Panel to debate potential solutions for decarbonising the regions energy systems and securing residents' future energy needs. The selection of panel members was undertaken by Sortition Foundation, which specialises in recruiting diverse groups of people to take part. The panel met to discuss how to achieve better energy security for the region including how we heat homes, how we travel and how we generate energy. The panel invited expert speakers to discuss various subjects related to Cornwall's energy system. The findings have been used to inform the development of the Cornwall and Isles of Scilly Local Area Energy Plan. https://letstalk.cornwall.gov.uk/laep . LAEP report: https://letstalk.cornwall.gov.uk/23871/widgets/105314/documents/68616",
