        "description": "Climate Literacy training for city, towns and parish councils, community groups and residents. The training was delivered by our partners GEP Environmental via online access. The training is a way of engaging our wider communities in addressing climate change, its impacts, and the importance of taking action. This empowers individuals to take action in their daily lives and provides them with the foundational knowledge to make more informed decisions. Delivering the training has fostered a sense of collective responsibility and community spirit. The training provides practical approaches to tackling climate change, with support on action planning. Participants gain the skills and confidence to implement effective solutions. This training also provides positive networking opportunities, bringing communities and organisations together. This training will be reviewed in late 2025/early 2026 for a 'refresh'. ",
