        "focusAreas": "Adaptation|Natural environment|Resilience|Agriculture|Energy|Emissions reduction",
        "description": "The Cornwall Voluntary Sector Climate and Environment Alliance was formed in September 2023 and includes a diverse range of 62 (and growing) organisations from across Cornwall. These organisations work within their specific communities on various challenges such as carbon reduction, litter picking, energy, and nature recovery. The alliance also includes larger organizations like Cornwall Wildlife Trust, Surfers Against Sewage, and the Eden Project. The alliance aims to support the voluntary, community, and social enterprise (VCSE) sector in adapting, mitigating, and building resilience against climate change. In the past year, they have collected baseline data from VCSE organizations and have published a \u201cGreen Footsteps Guide\u201d for VCSE organisations, to support positive action. The Council supports and engages with the group, attending meetings, events, and sharing key information. The Council has promoted the Green Footsteps Guide through its communication channels and contributed content to the webinar series that accompanies the written report. ",
