        "description": "Cornwall Council's 'Carbon Neutral Cornwall Hive' is an online engagement platform for residents and businesses in Cornwall. The web platform provides a space for people to learn from each other and be inspired to reduce greenhouse gas emissions for better human and environmental health. It shows what the Council is doing and what other organisations and communities are leading on across Cornwall. There is a discussion forum, an ideas bank, blog posts, and sections that signpost people to useful information, resources, and funding opportunities to help get low carbon and environmental projects underway. In early 2025, a survey was sent out to gather views on the future development of the Hive and meetings with external organisations was held to hear how they use the Hive and what they think could be improved. The results of the survey and meetings are informing a refresh of the Hive platform to make it even more useful. .\\n\\nAssociated with the Carbon Neutral Cornwall Hive is the Council-led Carbon Neutral Cornwall Newsletter - https://www.cornwall.gov.uk/environment/climate-emergency/climate-emergency-news/ - that shares what is happening across Cornwall to reduce greenhouse gas emissions - for the benefit of residents and the environment. It goes out every two months and showcases what the Council is leading on as well as initiatives led by external organisations and partners. Regular correspondence and meetings with local organisations helps in deciding the content for the newsletter.\\n",
