        "focusAreas": "Agriculture|Other: Skills|Industry|Building and Infrastructure|Energy",
        "description": "The Cornwall and Isles of Scilly Economic Forum (the Forum) is a group led by the private sector which advises Cornwall Council and the Council of the Isles of Scilly on economic priorities to create local jobs and drive growth. Members are drawn from a wide range of sectors and include representatives of Cornwall Council, which also provides the secretariat function. The Forum was created after the Government gave more control over economic development to local areas. Its goal is to provide a strong business perspective and local expertise to support the economic growth of Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. The Forum helps shape local economic strategies, evaluates public sector initiatives, and attracts investment to support growth and development projects. It works with the Local Authorities on strategic economic planning for Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly and the associated implementation of action and investment plans to drive sustainable and responsible economic and inclusive growth. A sub group, the Cornwall and Isles of Scilly Workforce and Skills Board, is currently developing a Workforce and Skills Strategy for Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. \\n\\nhttps://www.cornwall.gov.uk/business-trading-and-licences/economic-development/cornwall-and-isles-of-scilly-economic-forum/\\n",
        "otherEntities": "National government|Neighboring local government|Industry trade group|Academia"
