        "focusAreas": "Energy|Resilience|Adaptation|Emissions reduction",
        "description": "Working in collaboration with the WMCA on a number of projects including the development of the Local Area Energy Planning (LAEP) Tool a GIS for local and regional energy planning which is a progression from Coventry's Regional Eenrgy Systems Operator project funded by Innovate UK. https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/environment-energy/energy-capital/local-area-energy-planning/\\n\\nAlso Coventry as an ARP4 Pilot with WMCA as well contributed to the development of a regional and local GIS Climate Risk & Vulnerability Assessment (CRVA) Tool a geospatial tool capturing climate risks.https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/environment-energy/adapting-to-climate-change/climate-risk-and-adaptation-data-and-intelligence/\\n\\nActive member of the Regional Adaptation Network (RAN) https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/environment-energy/adapting-to-climate-change/regional-adaptation-network-ran/\\n\\nWorking with WMCA to secure the first infrastructure investment funding in the region from Great British Energy for \u00a3700K for connecting Sidney Stringer School and Coventry College to the City's Heat Network combined with a significant investment in solar renewables for rooftop solar. Also working with the Regional government on the development of a construction waste recycling facility.",
