        "focusAreas": "Ecosystem restoration|Food|Emissions reduction|Natural environment|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Building and Infrastructure|Resilience|Transport (Mobility)|Waste|Education|Adaptation|Industry|Landscape and jurisdictional approaches|Finance|Public health|Forestry|Energy|Water|Social Services",
        "description": "The City's independent Climate Change Board ( https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/environment-energy/adapting-to-climate-change/climate-risk-and-adaptation-data-and-intelligence/ ) consists of 25 private, public and third sector/charitable organisations with a shared commitment to the development and implementation of a Climate Change Strategy & Action Plan and also more recently a detailed Risk Assessment, Adaptation and Resilience Strategy and Plan and ARP4 Report to DEFRA https://www.coventry.gov.uk/climate-change/climate-change-adaptation-report-round-4/6. \\n\\nThe Board using the ICLEI 5 Pathways Framework has a Pathway Group for each which focuses on oversight , assessing needs and developing actions to increase the resilience of the City and its neighbourhood communities to extreme weather events. In addition to this work working with the Warwickshire Manufacturing Group and educational establishments in the City, the City Council developed with its partners a a Green Skills Roadmap https://www.coventry.gov.uk/employment-support/coventry-green-skills-roadmap/2\\n",
