        "focusAreas": null,
        "description": "Worked with the University of Warwick in the development of new track for the VLR service with the Warwickshire Manufacturing Group;\\nRetrofit Rocks working with schools in an innovative cross curricular education programme raising awareness of young children and families of what energy efficiency is all about and how grants can be accessed.\\nAlso working with behavioural economists on new approaches to promoting and increasing the take up of energy efficiency grants to homes. Over 2,000 households receiving benefit to date.\\nWorking with Coventry University Food growing and cooking projects e.g. Landed Kitchens , Coventry Grows creating accessible green spaces in deprived areas across the city may for food growing, wildlife conservation and amenity.\\nUniversity of Birmingham \u00a38.2m UKRI funded Indoor Air Quality applied research into the impacts of retrofit measures on damp condensation and mould along other potential emissions to inform future measures according to house srchetypes etc.",
