        "focusAreas": null,
        "description": "Development of Neighbourhood Resilience Groups to create community owned neighboruhood action plans in order to better respond and to mitigate the affects of extreme weather events heat, flood, etc.\\n\\nCoventry Grows supporting the development of green spaces across the City with over \u00a31m funding from National Lottery and Eon.\\n\\nJob shop working with low skilled and unemployed residents in providing training an work opportunities relating to energy efficiency and renewables with Westlands Contractor working with Citizen Housing and the City Council\\n\\nWorking with Coventry University on developing landed kitchens and community food growing projects.\\n\\nWorking closely with the Behavioural Economics Team at the University of Warwick for establishing ways of understanding the various market segments which exist across the City and through the use of focus groups to understand what are the barriers to the uptake of retrofit grants so that better targetting of messages and marketing campaigns to increase uptake of the the household retrofit programmes on offer. Also developed the use of Virtual Reality Headset Tours of real properties with images and comments from real houses and residents that the City Council Team (working with Eon and Citizen Housing) have retrofitted. Also running programmes for schools with the 'Retrofit Rocks' cross curricular primary school children & parental engagement project to explain what retrofitting is all about along with the benefits for the householder. retrofitting is all about https://warwick.ac.uk/research/partnerships/place-based-research/our-projects/placebasedresearchandculture/housingretrofitting/. \\n\\nEon the Strategic Energy Partner installing renewables in secondary schools and with the engagement of NEA to raise awareness and introduce retrofit activity and energy management as a STEM subject as a potential career path for young people. ",
