        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Adaptation|Natural environment",
        "description": "To support Protected Landscapes in meeting their potential nature, climate, people and place DEFRA have established ambitious targets for National Parks. These targets will promote the actions that are most needed to achieve positive changes. They will set the ambition for how Protected Landscapes should achieve 3 outcomes from the Environmental Improvement Plan (EIP) 2023.\\nGoal 1: Thriving plants and wildlife\\nGoal 2: Mitigating and adapting to climate change\\nGoal 3: Enhancing beauty, heritage and engagement with the natural environment \\nA range of indicators will be used to measure progress towards the targets and outcomes set out in the framework.\\n\\nNational Park Authorities should embed the targets into their statutory management plans. The national targets extend beyond the next five years and National Park Authorities are expected to develop bespoke interim targets and actions for the current 5 year plans period and a clear pathway for how the longer term targets will be achieved. \\n\\nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protected-landscapes-targets-and-outcomes-framework/protected-landscapes-targets-and-outcomes-framework\\n ",
