        "govtLevelsEngaged": "National-level government",
        "engagementPurpose": "Progress tracking and/or updates associated with this component are shared with a higher-level of government (e.g., via a digital platform)|To facilitate the integration of this component into the Nationally Determined Contribution (NDC)|To facilitate the integration of this component into assessments and policy developed across different levels of government|To facilitate capacity building across different levels of government|To facilitate information sharing across different levels of government|To collect data and/or feedback from other levels of government to inform its development",
        "comment": "Dundee City Council engages actively with the Scottish Climate Intelligence Service (SCIS), a national capacity-building programme funded jointly by the Scottish Government and all 32 Scottish local authorities through COSLA. SCIS is delivered through a partnership between the Edinburgh Climate Change Institute (ECCI) and the Improvement Service, with technical support from ClimateView and additional guidance from the Sustainable Scotland Network.\\nSCIS supports area-wide emissions reduction across all Scottish local authorities. Local authority carbon emissions are calculated using standardised methods to create robust baseline figures, which are then used within the ClimateView platform as a planning and communication tool for emissions reduction. Through this platform, Dundee can model interventions, track progress against national and local targets, and communicate results in a consistent and transparent way.\\nDundee's engagement with SCIS also includes participation in learning sessions and capacity-building activities with other local authorities, ensuring that city-wide climate action is informed by national-level expertise, aligns with Scottish Government targets, and is supported by standardised, evidence-based data. This collaboration strengthens Dundee's ability to plan, monitor, and report climate actions while contributing to Scotland's collective emissions reduction goals.\\n"
