        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Public health|Building and Infrastructure|Waste|Emissions reduction|Education|Adaptation|Ecosystem restoration|Transport (Mobility)|Water|Food|Landscape and jurisdictional approaches|Social Services|Industry|Energy|Natural environment|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Finance",
        "description": "Sustainable Scotland Network one of the best examples of engagement with the Scottish Government and other public bodies and Local Authorities. With Sustainability Officers engaging regularly with other public bodies at forums, workshops and knowledge sharing sessions. From this collaboration Dundee City Council and our Sustainability and Climate Change Team have welcomed the Scottish Government and UK Government on many occasions. In 2022, Dundee welcomed two high level Governmental Committees to the City. On the 12th of April 2022, The Climate Change Committee (CCC) UK visited and met with Dundee City Council Elected members, City Development Officers and other leaders from across the City. This visit was part of a nationwide tour to better understand the challenges and opportunities of delivering the country's net-zero emissions target. Findings from this visit were taken back to Westminster and Holyrood Parliaments (the Climate Change Committee advises governments on environmental policy). Visit documented here: https://www.dundeecity.gov.uk/news/article?article_ref=4335On the 5th of September, Dundee City Council hosted the Scottish Parliament's Net Zero, Energy and Transport Committee. This visit provided an opportunity for Dundee City Council leaders and the wider Sustainable Dundee Network partners to highlight the progress, opportunities and challenges the city faces in reaching net-zero, mitigating against climate change and ensuring a just transition in the City. The visit helped Dundee City Council to reach out to the Scottish Government and the UK Government, through the Net Zero, Energy and Transport Committee (the independent statutory body who advise both the UK Government and Scottish Government). The Net Zero, Energy and Transport Committee published the following report, 'THE ROLE OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT AND ITS CROSS-SECTORAL PARTNERS IN FINANCING AND DELIVERING A NET-ZERO SCOTLAND'. This report outlines the Committee visit to Dundee in September 2022. The full Committee report can be accessed using the link here: https://digitalpublications.parliament.scot/Committees/Report/NZET/2023/1/23/2c9752ff-eb3f-4273-8f78-e726676a3b6e#Introduction\u2003",
