        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction",
        "description": "Another example of collaboration is Dundee's active engagement in the Scottish Climate Intelligence Service (SCIS), a national initiative funded by the Scottish Government and all 32 Scottish local authorities through COSLA. SCIS is delivered through the Edinburgh Climate Change Institute (ECCI), the Improvement Service, and the Sustainable Scotland Network, with the ClimateOS platform (developed by ClimateView) providing the national data and modelling capability.\\n\\nThrough SCIS, Dundee has worked closely with national and local government partners to share knowledge, build capacity, and co-develop consistent approaches to climate planning. This has included participation in national workshops, peer-to-peer learning sessions, and joint development of data methodologies. The service provides a platform for local authorities to learn from one another, strengthen the evidence base for decision-making, and align local climate action with national policy objectives.\\n\\nDundee has also played a leadership role within this collaboration, having been the first local authority in Scotland to use the ClimateView (ClimateOS) platform in 2021, prior to SCIS being established. This early experience allowed Dundee to provide feedback on the platform's functionality and share practical insights with peers once the tool was rolled out nationally.\\n\\nBy contributing to and benefiting from SCIS, Dundee is helping to build a stronger, collective capacity for climate action across Scotland's local authorities, ensuring a more coordinated and evidence-led pathway to net zero.",
