        "comment": "ECC has worked with Sub National Transport Bodies including Transport East to develop a 'Carbon Playbook Tool', developed in discussion with Department for Transport to provide a consistent methodology for Local transport Authorities to define carbon baselines and assess the impacts of potential transport programmes. The carbon playbook tool is now available at https://qcrinfo.wordpress.com/\\nIt had been planned to use this to develop a long-term carbon trajectory for Essex linked to the delivery of the new local transport plan LTP4; however, Essex is now planning for devolution which will necessitate a Greater Essex LTP. Consequently, the new ECC LTP4 will not contain long term targets. Instead ECC will engage with Thurrock Council and Southend City Council to develop new baselines and trajectories for Greater Essex to discuss with the new Mayor and Mayoral Combined Authority members.\\n"
