        "focusAreas": "Energy|Emissions reduction|Building and Infrastructure|Resilience",
        "description": "The Low Carbon Across the South and East (LoCASE) programme was supported by the European Regional Development Fund to provide a free business support programme in the South and East of England. Its aim was to help businesses become more competitive and profitable while protecting the environment and encouraging low carbon solutions. To do this, LoCASE provided grants for businesses of up to 10,000, as well as training workshops and fully funded events. Targeted business support was on offer for companies which offer \u201cgreen\u201d or low carbon goods and services The programme started in 2016 and ended in mid-2023. Since its beginning 2.6m has been awarded to 397 businesses with an estimated 2,902 tonnes CO2 equivalent emissions reduction and 992,534 cost savings per annum within Greater Essex (including Southend and Thurrock). Further funding was secured for the partnership to extend the delivery of support to SMEs until June 2023, with an expected 2.7m of grants available to Greater Essex businesses. In Essex alone it has delivered support to over 460 businesses, annual savings of close to 1,400,000, and saved over 3,000 tonnes CO2e. Over 50 jobs have also been created as a result of this programme. We've already helped part fund the development and marketing of 87 new products and services.",
