        "mechanisms": "Knowledge or data sharing|Technical assistance|Economic development|Capacity development|Convening industry groups|Collaborative initiative",
        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Emissions reduction|Energy",
        "description": "ECC is a partner on the Ofgem Strategic Innovation Funded (SIF) SHIELD project. SHIELD stands for Smart Heat and Intelligent Energy in Low Income Districts and was designed to address the issue of a just transition for all in the journey toward net zero. SHIELD offers an innovative low carbon, affordable heat and energy solution for low income households. SHIELD seeks to combine various technologies, some established (PV and battery) and some novel (the Thermify HeatHub) (How it works - thermify, which captures waste heat from data processing activities and makes it available for affordable space and water heating within homes) to address the issue of fuel poverty. It will also explore the technological and financial possibilities of trading energy locally, creating new markets with both a social and a commercial focus. Funding to date has allowed for extensive modelling of proposed solutions, two instances of pilot technology installations and most recently a scale up of those trials over a four year period. SHIELD is delivered by a large partnership of organisations including UKPower Networks, ECC, UK Community Works CIC, Power Circle Projects Ltd and UK Power Networks, Citizens' Advice Essex, Thermify, Urban Chain and a number of social landlords.\\n",
