        "description": "The Business Climate Challenge supported small and medium-sized businesses to reduce their energy consumption by providing them with technical assistance to understand the measures they could take to operate their workplaces more efficiently. The programme worked with 203 workplaces from quarter 3 of 2022/3 to Quarter 4 of 2023/4 in partnership with nine business membership organisations and two NHS Integrated Care Boards that recruited 16 NHS GP Practices. Having completed delivery and evaluated the programme's design, delivery and impact, we are engaging with a pan-London group of boroughs and BIDs who meet to share experiences and learnings. The GLA disseminated lessons learnt, shared experiences with other programmes across the city and are still considering the opportunities to co-design a longer-term programme with Local Authorities, London Councils and wider stakeholders that could utilise any available funding and accelerate the scale and pace at which London's commercial buildings are decarbonised.",
