      "opportunitiesIdentified": "The transition to net zero represents a huge opportunity to secure livelihoods and grow new industries in the town, enhance social equality, and improve overall health and wellbeing. The council will also be able to reduce costs and improve its reputation.",
      "equitableDistribution": "Yes, the jurisdiction undertakes wider benefits and/or equity assessments for its climate actions",
      "quantifiesEquity": "Through Joint Strategic Needs Assessments and monitoring of a range of indicators, climate action impacts can be monitored. For example, data on the geographic location of unemployment related benefit claimants is regularly analysed. This can show hotspots of rises and falls in unemployment related benefit that could be an impact of climate action. ",
      "equityEvidence": "Community Engagement through the \\'big conversation\\' gave residents the opportunities to comment on their priorities. Residents were specifically asked about the councils priority for the area to be \\'sustainable, clean, safe and green\\'. The Council has an Equality, Diversity and Inclusion Policy and also requires detailed impact assessments for reports to Council Committees and Capital Projects "
