    "q1_3": {
      "oversightProcesses": "Council (or equivalent) is informed by relevant departments, committees and/or subcommittees about climate-related issues",
      "oversightDetails": "Approach to climate-related issues is led by the Net-Zero with Nature Programme Manager whose role includes: building capability and understanding across departments to improve decision making, delivering on specific climate related initiatives as outlined within the National Park Management Plan and reporting progress to leadership (Executive and Council Members) to inform of risks to progress and requirements for further investment.",
      "masterPlanningImpact": "Our Management Plan, Re:New Forest (https://www.newforestnpa.gov.uk/conservation/partnership-plan/partnership-plan-2021-2026/) has climate response as a specific theme. As such, we have identified actions that span all departments to increase resilience of the landscape to climate change as well as gathering momentum towards our target of net-zero with nature by 2050.\\n\\nClimate Change has been identified as a major issue for our forthcoming Local Development Plan which is being developed over the next year or so. We will be designing policy approaches to ensure development supports moves towards decarbonisation and climate resilience.",
      "financialPlanningImpact": "With climate-related issues being a key theme of our Management Plan, investment is being funnelled towards the climate response of the landscape via staff resource and infrastructure investments to achieve organisational net-zero emissions by 2030.",
      "transitionRisks": "Transition to a low-carbon economy potentially brings risk to areas such as negative impacts on the local tourism economy and societal exclusion of rural communities. A transition which is not inclusive may mean those in rural settings are disenfranchised or 'cut off' from changes to transport systems which support communities both in terms of access to goods and services and employment opportunities. Tourism is a large contributor to the local economy. A low-carbon economy which does not allow for this sector to access customers could be hugely detrimental to local prosperity. Agriculture plays a big role in the local economy as well, so any transition which disadvantages businesses in this sector, which in many cases are vulnerable to changes due to low (or negative) profit margins could see negative impacts on sustainable, nature-friendly food production."
    },
