        "description": "The Green New Deal fund is a ground-breaking low carbon investment fund that will invest 18 million in low carbon infrastructure in the region over the next four years, and can invest directly into SMEs to support business growth and innovation for the North East Combined Authority, a partnership between North Tyneside, Northumberland, Newcastle, Sunderland, South Tyneside, Gateshead, and Durham councils: https://www.amberinfrastructure.com/funds/the-green-new-deal-fund/ The partnership has commissioned consultancy Cambridge Econometrics to carry out a green economy and green jobs strategy and action plan for the area.\\n\\nNorth Tyneside Council are supporting the CA in the development of the revised Green New Deal Fund. \\n",
