        "mechanisms": "Collaborative initiative|Funding (grants)",
        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction|Energy|Building and Infrastructure",
        "description": "In partnership with E.ON, North Tyneside Council is delivering \u00a31.2 Million of matched funding via the Social Housing Decarbonisation Fund to improve efficiency within homes around the borough. This will mean that a total of \u00a32.4 million will be spent over the next 2 years and will go towards home improvements such as solar PV installations, Internal wall insulation and external wall insulation. The scheme has been introduced by the government to support our net zero initiative and will contribute to energy savings for our tenants. The authority has been successful in obtaining grant funding under Wave 2.1 (Social Housing Decarbonisation Fund) in partnership with E-On. Works will see 60 properties in Longbenton benefitting from external wall insulation and 21 properties in Benton benefitting from internal wall insulation. The project will also see 129 properties benefitting from Solar PV.",
