        "description": "North Tyneside Council are founding members of Net Zero North East, a collaborative and knowledge sharing partnership between the 7 North East local authorities, 2 combined authorities, the North East Local Enterprise Partnership and the North East Climate Coalition. It draws together data, evidence and the knowledge and perspectives of key partners to provide an assessment of the progress which has been made so far and identify future risks and opportunities. It focuses on each of the key action areas identified by the UK Government's Climate Change Committee (CCC).In support of the Paris climate targets and the UK Net Zero strategy, its aim is to deliver on the goal of achieving net zero carbon emissions at pace, whilst driving good quality jobs, improved standards of living and enhancement of the North East's unique regional environment. NZNEE is responsible for the North East Carbon and Nature Marketplace, which connects private buyers with sellers of high integrity natural capital projects. NZNEE's priorities are: Decarbonisation and the delivery of the North East's contribution to national and global net zero targets; Clean growth and opportunities for more and better jobs, underpinned by innovation; Environmental protection, restoration and improvement; and A 'just transition', leading to improvements in quality of life and growth that is inclusive for all in our region.",
