        "mechanisms": "Collaborative initiative|Funding (grants)",
        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction",
        "description": "Sustainable Lastingham is a community project convened by the NYMNPA and funded via the Net Zero Fund (North Yorkshire Council). It is partnership that seek to assess the feasibility of decarbonising deeply rural villages with a high level of heritage buildings. The project provides free bespoke, fabric-first retrofit assessments for 30 residential properties with the village as well as 3 community buildings. The project aims to equip residents with a broad range of retrofit options that are sensitive to the predominantly heritage buildings. Finding will feed into the the NYMNPA Planning Department's Design Guide and be made available to other Planning Authorities in the region.",
