        "description": "Analysing and reporting on the ten Protected Landscape Targets and Outcomes Framework targets as part of our management plan reporting. Incorporating these targets into our management plan. Apportionment of the following Protected Landscapes Targets and Outcomes Framework climate-related targets agreed between the Protected Landscapes.\\n\\nTarget 6:Reduce net greenhouse gas emissions in Protected Landscapes to net zero by 2050 relative to 1990 levels.\\nTarget 7: Peat: Restore approximately 130,000 hectares of peat in Protected Landscapes by 2050. \\nTarget 8: Increased tree canopy and woodland cover: Increase tree canopy and woodland cover (combined) by 3% of total land area in Protected Landscapes by 2050 (from 2022 baseline).\\n",
