        "engagementPurpose": "To facilitate the integration of this component into assessments and policy developed across different levels of government|To facilitate capacity building across different levels of government",
        "comment": "The North East and Yorkshire Net Zero Hub (NEY Net Zero Hub) is a collaboration between six Combined Authorities across the North East and Yorkshire. North Yorkshire Council engages regularly with representatives from the Hub. For example, the NEY Net Zero Hub is worked with DESNZ and the four other Net Zero Hubs, the council and other local partners to deliver the Local Energy Advice Demonstrator programme. Through this programme, North Yorkshire Council delivered a pilot project to overcome lack of confidence in retrofit and a lack of communication among installers. The scheme provided 178 Home Reports which received positive customer feedback, 160 training attendees on retrofit, design, renewables and builder training."
