        "focusAreas": "Finance|Agriculture|Industry|Ecosystem restoration|Public health|Education|Emissions reduction|Water|Energy|Natural environment|Building and Infrastructure|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Transport (Mobility)|Landscape and jurisdictional approaches|Resilience|Adaptation|Waste|Social Services|Forestry|Food",
        "description": "The council regularly engages with wider community partners including local climate advocacy groups. \\n\\nThis engagement has enabled successful funding bids for these group to deliver proactive projects. Dialogue has also been enabled, for example, during the development stages of the Climate Change Delivery Pathway two workshops were hosted by the Council to gather the thoughts and opinions of North Yorkshire's community environmental groups who now collectively go by the North Yorkshire Climate Coalition. The workshop provided our community partners to gain familiarity with the actions already proposed, comment on those actions, to propose new or alternative actions and targets, to consider how the actions may be prioritised and outline how their organisation could help the Council achieve the actions. ",
        "otherEntities": "Climate initiatives/networks|Agriculture|Utilities|Transport|Health Care|Education sector|Communication Services|Waste|Energy|Academia|Residents/community groups"
