        "focusAreas": "Transport (Mobility)|Water|Emissions reduction|Finance|Industry|Resilience|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Ecosystem restoration|Agriculture|Energy|Waste|Building and Infrastructure|Natural environment|Adaptation",
        "description": "North Yorkshire Council secured funding to develop a feasibility study and decarbonisation plan for Dalton Industrial Estate. Funding was secured via the Local Industrial Decarbonisation Plans Competition from Innovate UK, part of UK Research and Innovation, in collaboration with the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ). The project focused on five work packages: heat, power, transport, circular economy, and natural capital. This project required significant collaborative efforts across government levels. Businesses onsite at Dalton have been involved heavily and are responsible for developing work on each of the work packages bar natural capital which is being delivered by the Council. ",
