        "focusAreas": "Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Emissions reduction|Waste|Adaptation",
        "description": "Since its formation in 1992, the Nottingham Green Partnership (NGP) has united sustainability work across the city and coordinated efforts to build a greener future for Nottingham. It has continually sought to bring together partners from diverse sectors and fields of expertise to advance sustainable development, recognising that the whole is greater than the sum of its parts.\\n\\nIn 2019, the City's Carbon Neutral Charter and subsequent action plan in 2020 placed robust and sustainable city wide partnership working, collaboration and multiple organisational contributions as critical to Nottingham ever hoping to achieve the ambition to become the first city in the UK to be carbon neutral in 2028.\\n\\nIn order to make the NGP as effective as possible, the way it is governed, communicates and operates has been revised to ensure it is fit for purpose. The following are the areas that have been developed:\\n\\n1. Each partner provides a brief high level highlight report to the NGP each quarter to ensure there is clear visibility of the work being undertaken by all partner organisations. The report will focus on the work towards climate change that has been undertaken by their organisation. These reports will be provided on a quarterly basis and compiled as a summary for discussion at each NGP meeting. Individual partners will not be expected to present their reports. The information provided can be used to promote good news stories on a regular basis from across the city. A common report template was created for this purpose.\\n\\n2. NGP chair attends meetings of the City Council's CN28 Strategy Board and routinely reports progress of the partnership.\\n\\n3. 3 vice-chairs have been appointed for the NGP. These were appointed from the existing NGP membership through a process in which any application would be considered along with recommendations from two other NGP members. The vice-chairs will provide cover for the NGP chair in their absence, particularly at the CN28 Strategy Board.\\n\\n4. NCC has developed a website on behalf of the NGP. The content of the website is something the partnership actively contribute to and own.\\n\\n5. A new Terms of Reference for the NGP has been developed and adopted. \\n",
