        "comment": "The development of the Perth and Kinross Climate Change Risk and Opportunity Assessment included engagement with key stakeholders across Perth and Kinross such as Community Councils, local community groups, private sector enterprises and third sector organisations. The engagement included a workshop with all stakeholders identified which helped inform the final outcomes of the assessment. Following the publication of the assessment, a final workshop was organised to communicate the results to stakeholders and all Perth and Kinross residents. Additionally, a regional adaptation partnership (Climate Ready Tayside) was established in 2024 between Perth and Kinross Council, Angus Council and Dundee City Council to enable partnership working on climate adaptation and resilience. The PKC CCROA findings have therefore played a crucial role in the scope and action planning for Tayside Adapts."
