        "description": "Powys County Council and Powys PSB have been working closely on the development of a climate action plan to speed and scale climate action across the region. \\n Powys Council have an ambitious climate and nature emergency declarations will place Climate, biodiversity, and sustainability at the heart of its work. Committed to achieving net zero emissions as a Council by 2030, advancing its 30 X 30 nature and biodiversity goals. Simultaneously, assisting Powys communities in transitioning to a net-zero county through the implementation of Sustainable Powys.\\n\\nIncreased partnership working and collaboration with governments, partners, businesses, and communities through key pieces of work such as; regional energy planning (Powys LAEP), PSB Climate Wellbeing Plan, Marches Forward Partnership strategic decarbonisation planning, Severn Valley Water Management Scheme, Powys Nature Partnership, will help us collectively decarbonise our county and wider borders, embedding sustainability and resilience aligned with the Well-Being of Future Generations (Wales) Act objectives.\\n\\nThe PSB has been working closely with Officers and Powys Climate Stakeholder Group, which aims to help Powys play its part in tackling the climate crisis . This includes thirty-six people, representing many different groups and organisations including town and community councils, community groups and third sector organisations across the Powys region. ",
