        "comment": "The WMCA is a trailblazer combined authority, meaning it is one of two combined authorities who are in discussions with central government around a 'deeper devolution' deal for the region. The Trailblazer Devolution Deal, and following Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) for the Trailblazing Single Settlements for WMCA and GMCA (late 2023) documents, set out the framework for devolving energy, net zero and retrofit activities. The first devolved Integrated Settlement was agreed to begin on 1st April 2025.\\n\u00a3167m of retrofit funding for domestic and public sector buildings was included in the first three-year Integrated Settlement period. The targeted outcomes of this funding have been agreed as 14,000 social or low-income private homes upgraded to EPC C and an annual carbon emissions reductions from public buildings of 3.6ktCO2.\\nOngoing negotiations are seeking to extend the existing funding devolution arrangements and expand the Integrated Settlement's remit to other areas of spending - in particular, heat networks development funding.\\n\\nFurther negotiations will continue and there is hope that the devolution deal will broaden to include funding and powers for other programme areas, such as circular economy, climate adaptation, heat networks and air quality. "
