        "description": "Building on the success of the West Midlands Greener Together, which involved a Forum and a Citizens Panel (which, as a result of its success, has been adopted to support the entire organisation as well as environment and energy), and the community grant programmes, the WMCA has launched the Community Environment Network (CEN) in July 2025. The CEN aims to connect community groups working on environment action, boost their efforts, and also inspire and support new groups. The CEN is supporting communities groups to engage with the environment and climate change, increasing activity across the region and developing capacity for communities to increasingly lead climate action projects. The CEN is shaped and overseen by the CEN Advisory Group, who decide the Network's activities, funding allocation and ways to grow the Network and is made up of experts from a number of backgrounds. The CEN includes a support hub, with inspiration and resources to support community groups to take action, a series of events focusing on different aspects of environmental action and a 'small sparks grant' providing grants of up to \u00a3500 for communities to test new ideas or help move an existing project along. The CEN is bringing together community groups to collaborate, knowledge share and work together on greater climate action. More about the CEN can be found here: https://www.wmca.org.uk/what-we-do/environment-energy/community-environment-network/ ",
