        "description": "The WMCA runs the Net Zero Business Pledge as the organisation recognises that the region's businesses have a key role to play in reaching Net Zero by 2041. For the business, committing to the pledge will help them to:- Reduce your environmental impact and save costs- Position your business as a leader in the net zero carbon economy- Prepare your business for climate change impacts. The Business Pledge is administered by Sustainability West Midlands, who have created business networks and guidance to support the business on their pledge and commitment. This allows for a knowledge sharing function as well as a collaborative approach to tackling each businesses' emissions. The pledge continues to be developed, with a new interactive website completed: https://wmnetzeropledge.org.uk/\\n\\nOver 120 business in the region have pledged to be net zero. The Pledge operates a quarterly 'drop-in' session, where businesses attend to hear from experts, share ideas and innovations and network, to support each other on their net zero journey. ",
