        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction|Energy|Other: Fuel poverty",
        "description": "To support businesses in the West Midlands on their decarbonisation journey, Business Growth West Midlands (BGWM), an organisation set up by the WMCA to simplify regional business support with funding from the UK government through the UK Shared Prosperity Fund, has a Decarbonisation Net Zero programme (https://www.businessgrowthwestmidlands.org.uk/net-zero/). In affiliation with this programme the Business Energy Advice Service (BEAS), which is a government pilot offers businesses free expert support for sustainable growth through business advisors. BEAS aims to support sole traders, micro-businesses, small to medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), in reducing energy consumption and costs, which is done through: Information and advice (this includes 1-2-1 Advice, webinars, workshops, etc, on strategies on reducing carbon emissions and how they can get to net zero); Energy audits (free diagnostic tools/on-site carbon reduction surveys will be provided to support businesses to quantify and benchmark their emissions, identify cost-effective energy-saving measures, and set emissions targets); Knowledge transfer activities technical research and development (R&D) support focused on carbon accounting and sustainability software. \\nIn summary, a business can collaborate with this programme and receive free support and a free energy audit, to understand the energy demands of the business, through the Business Energy Advice Service (BEAS). The business can then apply for a 50% match funded grant of up to 100,000 to improve their energy efficiency and reduce their emissions. The grant could include solar panels, building insulation, water management, recycling and waste, heating (e.g. heat pumps) and energy-efficient lighting. To date, BEAS has provided a significant number of grants and record large estimated annual carbon savings.\\n By the end of the programme, over 4,000 businesses in the region will have received at least an energy audit.\\n",
